In order to inculcate the neces- sity 01 great caution in the profession 01 will-hunting, Tiresias, in oracular style, predicts an event which had probably actually happened at Rome in Horace's own day. One Nasica, who had a tall daughter, gave her in marriage to a rich old man, Coranus, expecting to be remembered in his will.
